page.title: 09 Osborne House Visit
page.content:
On Monday 15th July we went to visit{Osborne House.} We left school at 10.40 and after a 15 minute walk we arrived at the gate to the House. We asked the security guard for Mr Underwood and were directed to the main House. We soon found the reception desk and after a little wait he arrived and showed us the way to the Education Room. This is were we started to ask our questions:
1). Who built the extensions to the House? {Thomas Cubit } 2). How old is the House? {Coming up to 140 years old} 3). Where are the most valuable objects in the House? {In the Durbar Room 4). Which the the favourite room? {The Private Sitting Room
